> This dish is so quick and easy, it will become your go-to weeknight meal. Garlicky beans and sweet caramelized onions are topped with crumbly goats cheese, all over warm ciabatta. We served it with roasted broccollini.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve the @grape tomatoes{1%bunch}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve the @lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Chop the @oregano{1%sprig}. Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%can}. Cut the bottom inch off of the @baby broccoli{1%bunch} and discard.

Toss the broccolini with 1 tablespoon @olive oil{2%tablespoon} and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Spread on a #baking sheet{} and roast until crisp-tender, tossing halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a #non-stick pan{} over medium heat. Add the onions and season with salt and pepper. Cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until softened.

Add the tomatoes and cook for another ~{5%minutes}, until they start to burst. Set aside.

Add the cannellini beans to the pan with oregano, garlic, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, until fragrant.

Halve the @ciabatta roll{1} lengthwise and toast it in the oven for about ~{4%minutes}, until crispy.

Top with tomato, onion, and cannellini beans. Sprinkle @crumbled goat cheese{2%ounce} on top. Serve with roasted broccolini to the side with a squeeze of lemon.